Manchester United boss Louis van Gaal has won a trophy in his first season at every club he's managed, except for AZ Alkmaar.

United lost 2-1 against Arsenal in the FA Cup quarter-final on Monday night at Old Trafford, all but ending Van Gaal's search for silverware in his debut season in England.

Van Gaal won the Uefa Cup with Ajax in his first year, the La Liga title with Barcelona and the Bundesliga and DFB Cup with Bayern Munich previously.

