The Dutchman's night only got worse on Monday as former United players showed what they were lacking at the Theatre of Dreams. 

Nani scored for Sporting Lisbon, Paul Pogba sent Juventus 11 points clear at the top of Serie A with a screamer, and it was Danny Welbeck who found the winner for Arsenal at Old Trafford.

United will now concentrate on finishing in the top four of the Premier League as they fight with Arsenal, Liverpool, Tottenham Hotspur and Southampton for Champions League qualification.

